The ANC in KwaZulu-Natal has called on the security company responsible to take action against two bodyguards after threatening video emerged on social media.The video revealed the two armed bodyguards allegedly working for an ANC member, making death threats while cocking guns.&#8220;The African National Congress in KwaZulu-Natal has been exposed to a disturbing circulating video in which security guards of the ANC eThekwini Regional comrade Bheki Ntuli are displaying firearms and high calibre assault rifle.&#8220;The African National Congress strongly denounces and distances itself from this irresponsible display of weapons, irrespective of the purpose for which it was done, said ANC Provincial spokesperson Mdumiseni Ntuli.It is not yet clear when and where the video was recorded. @MbalulaFikile&#8230;any comment??? pic.twitter.com/CnoQqUBfO0&mdash; Mpho Tsedu (@MphoTsedu) September 7, 2017The video comes days after the death of Sindiso Magaqa, who was a ward councillor in Umzimkhulu in southern KwaZulu-Natal.Magaqa, 35, died at the Albert Luthuli Hospital in Durban two months after he was shot in a suspected ambush.TNA Reporter 